<section xml:id="section-hello-world" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Hello World!</title>
  <p>
    Here is a very basic <q>Hello World!</q> PG problem.
    It does nothing except print <q>Hello World!</q>.
  </p>

  <listing>
      <caption>Hello World!</caption>
      <program language="perl">
          <input><xi:include href="../assets/pg/hello-world.pg" parse="text"/></input>
      </program>
  </listing>

  <exercise>
    <!-- For now, have to manually copy the pg file to host course -->
    <webwork source="pg/hello-world.pg"/>
  </exercise>

  <p>
    Note the file starts with <c>DOCUMENT();</c> and ends with <c>ENDDOCUMENT();</c>.
    The <c>loadMacros()</c> command is loading two fundamnetal macro libraries you
    will almost always want to load. Thee problem statement itself is in between
    <c>BEGIN_PGML</c> and <c>END_PGML</c>.
  </p>

</section>
